Mitchell John Benn known as Mitch Benn is a British musician, comedian and author. He played minor roles in the more recent phases of the radio series, including Left Brain and Thor in the Hexagonal Phase, and in September 2013 he played the role of Zaphod Beeblebrox in the touring production of "The Hitchhiker's Guide To The Galaxy Live Radio Show"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Live! 2013 Tour - YouTube.

He has had regular features on BBC Radio 4 and BBC Radio 2, and is most known for his stand-up comedy and comedy rock. He has released eight albums (as of 2018) and performed at several music festivals and comedy venues, including the Edinburgh Festival Fringe. 

He has appeared almost exclusively in comedy roles on radio and television, including appearances on the channels Comedy Central and CBBC, but he also appeared in an episode of Merlin. Radio 
